<BaseLayout title="Prompt Structure" description="Learn the subject, action, clothing, scene, camera, and lighting order for AI image prompts." canonicalPath="/guides/prompt-structure/"><article class="content-section article-body"><h1>Prompt Structure: Subject, Action, Clothing, Scene, Camera, Lighting</h1><p>A stable prompt usually moves from the main subject to the surrounding context. The Atlas order is subject, pose or action, clothing, scene, camera angle, lighting, mood, style direction, and quality tags.</p><p>This order keeps the image goal readable. If the prompt becomes noisy, remove weak phrases first. Strong subject and camera language usually matter more than another broad quality tag.</p></article></BaseLayout>
